pulfalight.title: Button for Zip Files should say "Download Content"
Add Panopto viewer if given appropriate DAO

comments.body: @tpendragon We are not looking into this language specifically in our upcoming usability tests. As @hackartisan mentioned, the "View Content" button is displayed when there's a link to external content. Does the button provide additional functionality to users that the viewer doesn't provide, such as the ability to download? If not, I would hide the "View Content" button in the Panopto context.
@sdellis Yes, that link is the full content download.

@tpendragon in that case, "Download Content" seems more appropriate than "View Content" as a button label when the Panopto viewer is displayed. "Download Video" (and "Download Audio") would be even better if we have that much information about the content.

Button with label from DAO:
